result.execSummary:
The defendant Dustin Lee R.J. Miller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ma] Case called at 9:01am 
Defendant Dustin Lee R.J. Miller appeared by zoom.  Attorney Amber K. Rumpf appeared by zoom for Dustin Lee R.J. Miller.  Attorney Brookellen Teuber in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived

Maximum penalties are recited; Constitutional rights are reviewed; plea of " NO CONTEST " entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated. The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #2 and #3.

Sentencing recommendations/ arguments given by Counsel 

On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence and places the Defendant on Probation for 3 years, with conditions:
--comply with all terms and conditions of Fond du Lac Drug Treatment Court program
--follow through with all AODA  treatment per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling per Agent
--random drug and/or alcohol screening
--no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--take any and all prescription medications only as prescribed by treating prescriber
--if permitted to travel out of State, no possession or use of marijuana(THC) in states where it is legal. No legal CBD products or other legal cannabis derivatives without express written permission of agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision 
--payment of costs, fees and surcharges, to include $50 drug testing fee

Days credit for time already served:  10  days
